nodes.text: Leeanna Walsman (born November 22, 1979) is an Australian actress who portrayed the bounty hunter Zam Wesell in Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones. She later reprised her role in the video game Star Wars: Bounty Hunter.
Walsman was discovered by Robin Gurland, the casting director for Attack of the Clones, while she was performing with Rose Byrne (Dormé) in the play La Dispute for the Sydney Theatre Company.

Walsman shared screen with Star Wars co-star Graeme Blundell (Ruwee Naberrie) in the 2000 film Looking for Alibrandi. She also worked with Joel Edgerton (Owen Lars in Episode II and Episode III) and Claudia Karvan (Sola Naberrie) in the stop motion film $9.99.
